{
  "body": "``` patch\nSubject: [PATCH] eliminate prose about hypertext mechanics, add unembedded\n vector image\n\n* shorter is more usable, see\n  <http://www.joelonsoftware.com/uibook/chapters/fog0000000062.html> about half\n  way down the length of the article\n* <http://www.quut.com/berlin/ht/writing/text.html>\n* <http://www.w3.org/Provider/Style/NoMechanics>\n\n---\n htmlify.p6 | 18 +++++++++++-------\n 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+), 7 deletions(-)\n\ndiff --git a/htmlify.p6 b/htmlify.p6\nindex 7d869a7..0ce75ed 100755\n--- a/htmlify.p6\n+++ b/htmlify.p6\n@@ -238,15 +238,19 @@ multi write-type-source($doc) {\n     }\n\n     if $type {\n-        my $tg-preamble = qq[<h1>Type graph</h1>\\n<p>Below you should see a\n-        clickable image showing the type relations for $podname that links\n-        to the documentation pages for the related types. If not, try the\n-        <a href=\"/images/type-graph-{uri_escape $podname}.png\">PNG\n-        version</a> instead.</p>];\n         $pod.contents.append: Pod::Raw.new(\n             target => 'html',\n-            contents => $tg-preamble ~ svg-for-file(\"html/images/type-graph-$podname.svg\"),\n-\n+            contents => qq[<h1>Type graph</h1>\n+<figure>\n+<figcaption>Type relations for <code>$podname</code></figcaption>] ~\n+                svg-for-file(\"html/images/type-graph-$podname.svg\") ~\n+                qq[<p class=\"fallback\">stand-alone image:\n+        <a rel=\"alternate\" href=\"/images/type-graph-{uri_escape $podname}.svg\"\n+            type=\"image/svg+xml\">vector</a>,\n+        <a rel=\"alternate\" href=\"/images/type-graph-{uri_escape $podname}.png\"\n+            type=\"image/png\">raster</a>\n+    </p>\n+</figure>]\n         );\n\n         my @mro = $type.mro;\n-- \n2.1.4\n```\n\nI have not tested the code.\n\nIf you wish to, it is possible to hide the `figure > p.fallback` element after [feature detection for embedded SVG](https://css-tricks.com/a-complete-guide-to-svg-fallbacks/#fallback-inline-svg-testing), but I don't think it's necessary. These fallback links are useful even if the embedded figure can be displayed.\n",
